{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841692717,"sessionID":"ses_287965c48ffeBA0bj1XqfDCEYv","part":{"id":"prt_d7869cbf3001ENQSeER9WuAc3A","messageID":"msg_d7869b099001vsH9l4jHQoLsgi","sessionID":"ses_287965c48ffeBA0bj1XqfDCEYv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c927c946afcd415191d2ad15f9a49d58","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量\n2: \n3: Module: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`  \n4: Language: Go  \n5: Size: S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define shared types, constants, and CRD structures for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### REQ-001: Protocol Type Constants\n18: \n19: **GIVEN** the `shared_types.go` file defines protocol types for network ports  \n20: **WHEN** a developer needs to specify HTTP or HTTPS protocol  \n21: **THEN** the `ProtocolType` type and constants `ProtocolTypeHTTP` and `ProtocolTypeHTTPS` shall be available\n22: \n23: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n24: \n25: ```go\n26: // Scenario 1: HTTP protocol constant\n27: GIVEN the package v1alpha1 is imported\n28: WHEN ProtocolTypeHTTP is referenced\n29: THEN it shall equal \"HTTP\"\n30: \n31: // Scenario 2: HTTPS protocol constant\n32: GIVEN the package v1alpha1 is imported\n33: WHEN ProtocolTypeHTTPS is referenced\n34: THEN it shall equal \"HTTPS\"\n35: \n36: // Scenario 3: Protocol type can be used in struct fields\n37: GIVEN a TargetPort struct with Protocol field\n38: WHEN assigning ProtocolTypeHTTP to Protocol\n39: THEN the value shall serialize to JSON as \"HTTP\"\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ### REQ-002: Auth Mode Type Constants\n45: \n46: **GIVEN** the `shared_types.go` file defines authentication modes for CodeInterpreter  \n47: **WHEN** a developer needs to specify authentication mode  \n48: **THEN** the `AuthModeType` type and constants `AuthModePicoD` and `AuthModeNone` shall be available\n49: \n50: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n51: \n52: ```go\n53: // Scenario 1: PicoD auth mode constant\n54: GIVEN the package v1alpha1 is imported\n55: WHEN AuthModePicoD is referenced\n56: THEN it shall equal \"picod\"\n57: \n58: // Scenario 2: None auth mode constant\n59: GIVEN the package v1alpha1 is imported\n60: WHEN AuthModeNone is referenced\n61: THEN it shall equal \"none\"\n62: \n63: // Scenario 3: Auth mode validation via kubebuilder\n64: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterSpec with AuthMode field\n65: WHEN setting AuthMode to an invalid value\n66: THEN kubebuilder validation Enum shall reject values other than \"picod\" or \"none\"\n67: ```\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ### REQ-003: TargetPort Shared Struct\n72: \n73: **GIVEN** `TargetPort` defines network port configuration for exposing sandbox services  \n74: **WHEN** a CRD needs to specify exposed ports  \n75: **THEN** the struct shall contain PathPrefix, Name, Port, and Protocol fields with proper JSON tags and validation\n76: \n77: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n78: \n79: ```go\n80: // Scenario 1: TargetPort JSON serialization\n81: GIVEN a TargetPort with all fields populated\n82: WHEN marshaling to JSON\n83: THEN the output shall contain \"pathPrefix\", \"name\", \"port\", \"protocol\" keys\n84: \n85: // Scenario 2: TargetPort Protocol default\n86: GIVEN a TargetPort with Protocol field\n87: WHEN kubebuilder processes the struct\n88: THEN the default value shall be \"HTTP\"\n89: \n90: // Scenario 3: TargetPort Protocol enum validation\n91: GIVEN a TargetPort with Protocol field\n92: WHEN kubebuilder processes the struct\n93: THEN only \"HTTP\" and \"HTTPS\" values shall be allowed\n94: \n95: // Scenario 4: TargetPort DeepCopy\n96: GIVEN a TargetPort instance with all fields set\n97: WHEN calling DeepCopy()\n98: THEN a deep copy with identical values shall be returned\n99: AND modifying the copy shall not affect the original\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### REQ-004: GroupVersion and Scheme Registration\n105: \n106: **GIVEN** the API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n107: **WHEN** types need to be registered with Kubernetes runtime scheme  \n108: **THEN** `GroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, and `AddToScheme` shall be available\n109: \n110: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n111: \n112: ```go\n113: // Scenario 1: GroupVersion group\n114: GIVEN the v1alpha1 package\n115: WHEN accessing GroupVersion.Group\n116: THEN it shall equal \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n117: \n118: // Scenario 2: GroupVersion version\n119: GIVEN the v1alpha1 package\n120: WHEN accessing GroupVersion.Version\n121: THEN it shall equal \"v1alpha1\"\n122: \n123: // Scenario 3: AddToScheme function\n124: GIVEN the v1alpha1 package\n125: WHEN accessing AddToScheme\n126: THEN it shall be a non-nil function of type func(*runtime.Scheme) error\n127: \n128: // Scenario 4: SchemeBuilder\n129: GIVEN the v1alpha1 package\n130: WHEN accessing SchemeBuilder\n131: THEN it shall be a non-nil pointer to scheme.Builder\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ### REQ-005: Kind Constants and GroupVersionKind Helpers\n137: \n138: **GIVEN** CRD types need Kind constants for type identification  \n139: **WHEN** a controller or client needs to reference CRD kinds  \n140: **THEN** Kind constants and GroupVersionKind helpers shall be available\n141: \n142: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n143: \n144: ```go\n145: // Scenario 1: AgentRuntime kind constant\n146: GIVEN the v1alpha1 package\n147: WHEN accessing AgentRuntimeKind\n148: THEN it shall equal \"AgentRuntime\"\n149: \n150: // Scenario 2: AgentRuntimeList kind constant\n151: GIVEN the v1alpha1 package\n152: WHEN accessing AgentRuntimeListKind\n153: THEN it shall equal \"AgentRuntimeList\"\n154: \n155: // Scenario 3: AgentRuntime GroupVersionKind\n156: GIVEN the v1alpha1 package\n157: WHEN accessing AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind\n158: THEN it shall have Group \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version \"v1alpha1\", Kind \"AgentRuntime\"\n159: \n160: // Scenario 4: CodeInterpreter kind constant\n161: GIVEN the v1alpha1 package\n162: WHEN accessing CodeInterpreterKind\n163: THEN it shall equal \"CodeInterpreter\"\n164: \n165: // Scenario 5: CodeInterpreterList kind constant\n166: GIVEN the v1alpha1 package\n167: WHEN accessing CodeInterpreterListKind\n168: THEN it shall equal \"CodeInterpreterList\"\n169: \n170: // Scenario 6: CodeInterpreter GroupVersionKind\n171: GIVEN the v1alpha1 package\n172: WHEN accessing CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind\n173: THEN it shall have Group \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version \"v1alpha1\", Kind \"CodeInterpreter\"\n174: ```\n175: \n176: ---\n177: \n178: ### REQ-006: Resource Helper Function\n179: \n180: **GIVEN** controllers need GroupVersionResource for informers and listers  \n181: **WHEN** constructing a GroupVersionResource for a resource name  \n182: **THEN** the `Resource()` helper function shall return the correct GVR\n183: \n184: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n185: \n186: ```go\n187: // Scenario 1: AgentRuntime resource\n188: GIVEN the Resource function\n189: WHEN calling Resource(\"agentruntimes\")\n190: THEN it shall return GroupVersionResource with Group \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\" and Resource \"agentruntimes\"\n191: \n192: // Scenario 2: CodeInterpreter resource\n193: GIVEN the Resource function\n194: WHEN calling Resource(\"codeinterpreters\")\n195: THEN it shall return GroupVersionResource with Group \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\" and Resource \"codeinterpreters\"\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ### REQ-007: AgentRuntime CRD Types\n201: \n202: **GIVEN** AgentRuntime represents a runtime configuration for an AI agent sandbox  \n203: **WHEN** defining the CRD structure  \n204: **THEN** `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus`, `SandboxTemplate`, and `AgentRuntimeList` shall be properly defined\n205: \n206: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n207: \n208: ```go\n209: // Scenario 1: AgentRuntime struct embedding\n210: GIVEN an AgentRuntime instance\n211: WHEN accessing metadata\n212: THEN metav1.TypeMeta and metav1.ObjectMeta shall be embedded\n213: \n214: // Scenario 2: AgentRuntimeSpec required fields\n215: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeSpec\n216: WHEN validating the spec\n217: THEN Ports (targetPort in JSON), Template (podTemplate in JSON), SessionTimeout, and MaxSessionDuration shall be required\n218: \n219: // Scenario 3: AgentRuntimeSpec default values\n220: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeSpec without timeout values\n221: WHEN kubebuilder applies defaults\n222: THEN SessionTimeout shall default to \"15m\" AND MaxSessionDuration shall default to \"8h\"\n223: \n224: // Scenario 4: AgentRuntimeStatus conditions\n225: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeStatus\n226: WHEN accessing Conditions\n227: THEN it shall be a slice of metav1.Condition with atomic list type\n228: \n229: // Scenario 5: SandboxTemplate PodSpec\n230: GIVEN a SandboxTemplate\n231: WHEN creating a sandbox pod\n232: THEN Spec field shall contain corev1.PodSpec for the pod definition\n233: \n234: // Scenario 6: AgentRuntime DeepCopy\n235: GIVEN an AgentRuntime with populated fields\n236: WHEN calling DeepCopy()\n237: THEN a deep copy with identical values shall be returned\n238: AND modifying nested maps/slices in the copy shall not affect the original\n239: \n240: // Scenario 7: AgentRuntime DeepCopyObject\n241: GIVEN an AgentRuntime instance\n242: WHEN calling DeepCopyObject()\n243: THEN it shall return a runtime.Object that is a deep copy\n244: \n245: // Scenario 8: AgentRuntimeList DeepCopy\n246: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeList with items\n247: WHEN calling DeepCopy()\n248: THEN items slice shall be deeply copied\n249: \n250: // Scenario 9: AgentRuntime JSON field names\n251: GIVEN an AgentRuntimeSpec marshaled to JSON\n252: WHEN inspecting the JSON\n253: THEN \"targetPort\" shall be used for Ports field AND \"podTemplate\" shall be used for Template field\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ### REQ-008: CodeInterpreter CRD Types\n259: \n260: **GIVEN** CodeInterpreter represents a specialized runtime for code execution  \n261: **WHEN** defining the CRD structure  \n262: **THEN** `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, and `CodeInterpreterList` shall be properly defined\n263: \n264: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n265: \n266: ```go\n267: // Scenario 1: CodeInterpreter struct embedding\n268: GIVEN a CodeInterpreter instance\n269: WHEN accessing metadata\n270: THEN metav1.TypeMeta and metav1.ObjectMeta shall be embedded\n271: \n272: // Scenario 2: CodeInterpreterSpec required fields\n273: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterSpec\n274: WHEN validating the spec\n275: THEN Template field shall be required\n276: \n277: // Scenario 3: CodeInterpreterSpec default values\n278: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterSpec without defaults\n279: WHEN kubebuilder applies defaults\n280: THEN SessionTimeout shall default to \"15m\" AND MaxSessionDuration shall default to \"8h\" AND AuthMode shall default to \"picod\"\n281: \n282: // Scenario 4: CodeInterpreterSpec optional fields\n283: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterSpec\n284: WHEN optional fields are not set\n285: THEN Ports, WarmPoolSize, and AuthMode may be nil/empty\n286: \n287: // Scenario 5: CodeInterpreterSpec AuthMode validation\n288: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterSpec\n289: WHEN setting AuthMode\n290: THEN kubebuilder shall only accept \"picod\" or \"none\" values\n291: \n292: // Scenario 6: CodeInterpreterStatus Ready field\n293: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterStatus\n294: WHEN accessing Ready field\n295: THEN it shall be a boolean indicating readiness\n296: \n297: // Scenario 7: CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate image field\n298: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate\n299: WHEN specifying container image\n300: THEN Image field shall be available (optional with empty string default)\n301: \n302: // Scenario 8: CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate resource fields\n303: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate\n304: WHEN configuring the container\n305: THEN RuntimeClassName, ImagePullPolicy, ImagePullSecrets, Environment, Command, Args, and Resources shall be available\n306: \n307: // Scenario 9: CodeInterpreter DeepCopy\n308: GIVEN a CodeInterpreter with populated fields\n309: WHEN calling DeepCopy()\n310: THEN a deep copy with identical values shall be returned\n311: AND modifying nested pointers in the copy shall not affect the original\n312: \n313: // Scenario 10: CodeInterpreter DeepCopyObject\n314: GIVEN a CodeInterpreter instance\n315: WHEN calling DeepCopyObject()\n316: THEN it shall return a runtime.Object that is a deep copy\n317: \n318: // Scenario 11: CodeInterpreterList DeepCopy\n319: GIVEN a CodeInterpreterList with items\n320: WHEN calling DeepCopy()\n321: THEN items slice shall be deeply copied\n322: ```\n323: \n324: ---\n325: \n326: ### REQ-009: Kubernetes API Machinery Integration\n327: \n328: **GIVEN** types must integrate with Kubernetes API machinery  \n329: **WHEN** generating client code and CRD manifests  \n330: **THEN** proper kubebuilder markers and deepcopy-gen markers shall be present\n331: \n332: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n333: \n334: ```go\n335: // Scenario 1: AgentRuntime runtime.Object implementation\n336: GIVEN the generated zz_generated.deepcopy.go\n337: WHEN checking AgentRuntime\n338: THEN it shall implement runtime.Object interface via DeepCopyObject\n339: \n340: // Scenario 2: CodeInterpreter runtime.Object implementation\n341: GIVEN the generated zz_generated.deepcopy.go\n342: WHEN checking CodeInterpreter\n343: THEN it shall implement runtime.Object interface via DeepCopyObject\n344: \n345: // Scenario 3: Kubebuilder resource scope\n346: GIVEN AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types\n347: WHEN generating CRD manifests\n348: THEN both shall have Namespaced scope\n349: \n350: // Scenario 4: Kubebuilder status subresource\n351: GIVEN AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types\n352: WHEN generating CRD manifests\n353: THEN both shall have status subresource enabled\n354: \n355: // Scenario 5: Kubebuilder printcolumn\n356: GIVEN AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types\n357: WHEN generating CRD manifests\n358: THEN \"Age\" column shall be displayed from .metadata.creationTimestamp\n359: ```\n360: \n361: ---\n362: \n363: ## Implementation Files\n364: \n365: | File | Purpose |\n366: |------|---------|\n367: | `shared_types.go` | ProtocolType, AuthModeType, TargetPort definitions |\n368: | `agentruntime_types.go` | AgentRuntime, AgentRuntimeSpec, AgentRuntimeStatus, SandboxTemplate, AgentRuntimeList |\n369: | `codeinterpreter_types.go` | CodeInterpreter, CodeInterpreterSpec, CodeInterpreterStatus, CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, CodeInterpreterList |\n370: | `groupversion_info.go` | GroupVersion, SchemeBuilder, AddToScheme |\n371: | `register.go` | Kind constants, GroupVersionKind helpers, Resource helper |\n372: | `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Generated DeepCopy implementations |\n373: | `types_test.go` | Unit tests for all types |\n374: \n375: ---\n376: \n377: ## Dependencies\n378: \n379: - `k8s.io/api/core/v1` - Core Kubernetes API types (PodSpec, etc.)\n380: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` - ObjectMeta, TypeMeta, Duration, Condition\n381: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` - runtime.Object interface\n382: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema` - GroupVersion, GroupVersionResource\n383: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/scheme` - SchemeBuilder\n384: \n385: ---\n386: \n387: ## Validation Checklist\n388: \n389: - [ ] All type constants have correct string values\n390: - [ ] All structs have correct JSON tags for Kubernetes API\n391: - [ ] All kubebuilder markers are present for CRD generation\n392: - [ ] DeepCopy methods correctly deep-copy all nested structures\n393: - [ ] DeepCopyObject returns correct type for runtime.Object interface\n394: - [ ] GroupVersion matches API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n395: - [ ] Resource helper returns correct GroupVersionResource\n396: - [ ] All unit tests in `types_test.go` pass\n\n(End of file - total 396 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量\n\nModule: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`  \nLanguage: Go  \nSize: S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine shared types, constants, and CRD structures for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Protocol Type Constants\n\n**GIVEN** the `shared_types.go` file defines protocol types for network ports  \n**WHEN** a developer needs to specify HTTP or HTTPS protocol  ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775841692694,"end":1775841692715}}}}
