{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841737722,"sessionID":"ses_287965c48ffeBA0bj1XqfDCEYv","part":{"id":"prt_d786a77b5001Wrwrona3gnXvQ5","messageID":"msg_d786a5709001KK7UOKMwSrNa57","sessionID":"ses_287965c48ffeBA0bj1XqfDCEYv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-95107a9cd6a741408f08fee4577efce9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-1 pending] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Project Setup\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1** Create directory structure `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n20:   - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`\n21:   - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/`\n22: \n23: - [ ] **T1.2** Add dependency `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` to `go.mod`\n24:   - Verify: `go get github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 && go mod tidy`\n25: \n26: ### Phase 2: Core Type Definitions\n27: \n28: - [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n29:   - Define `ErrorResponse` struct\n30:   - Define `SuccessResponse` struct\n31:   - Define `HandleError` function\n32:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/`\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T2.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/config.go`\n35:   - Define `Config` struct with fields: `Addr`, `ReadTimeout`, `WriteTimeout`, `IdleTimeout`, `ShutdownTimeout`, `EnableHealthz`, `EnableReadyz`\n36:   - Define `DefaultConfig()` function\n37:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/`\n38: \n39: ### Phase 3: Router Implementation\n40: \n41: - [ ] **T3.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go`\n42:   - Import `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5`\n43:   - Define `Router` struct wrapping `chi.Router`\n44:   - Implement `NewRouter()` constructor\n45:   - Implement `RegisterHandlers(handlers ...Handler)` method\n46:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/`\n47: \n48: ### Phase 4: Handler Interface & Health Handler\n49: \n50: - [ ] **T4.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go`\n51:   - Define `Handler` interface with `Register(r chi.Router)` method\n52:   - Define `HandlerFunc` type and `ServeHTTP` implementation\n53:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`\n54: \n55: - [ ] **T4.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go`\n56:   - Define `HealthChecker` interface with `IsHealthy()` and `IsReady()` methods\n57:   - Define `HealthHandler` struct with `checker` field\n58:   - Implement `NewHealthHandler(checker HealthChecker)` constructor\n59:   - Implement `Register(r chi.Router)` method\n60:   - Implement `healthz(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)` handler\n61:   - Implement `readyz(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)` handler\n62:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`\n63: \n64: ### Phase 5: Middleware Implementation\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T5.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go`\n67:   - Define `LoggingMiddleware` struct with `logger` field\n68:   - Implement `NewLoggingMiddleware(logger Logger)` constructor\n69:   - Implement `Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler` method\n70:   - Define `responseWriterWrapper` struct to capture status code\n71:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/`\n72: \n73: - [ ] **T5.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go`\n74:   - Define `RecoveryMiddleware` struct with `logger` field\n75:   - Implement `NewRecoveryMiddleware(logger Logger)` constructor\n76:   - Implement `Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler` method\n77:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/`\n78: \n79: - [ ] **T5.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go`\n80:   - Define `CORSMiddleware` struct with config fields\n81:   - Implement `NewCORSMiddleware(...)` constructor\n82:   - Implement `Wrap(next http.Handler) http.Handler` method\n83:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/`\n84: \n85: ### Phase 6: Server Implementation\n86: \n87: - [ ] **T6.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n88:   - Define `HTTPServer` struct with fields: `server`, `router`, `config`, `handlers`, `logger`, `stopCh`\n89:   - Implement `NewHTTPServer(cfg Config, logger Logger) *HTTPServer` constructor\n90:   - Implement `RegisterHandler(name string, h Handler)` method\n91:   - Implement `setupRouter()` private method\n92:   - Implement `setupMiddleware()` private method\n93:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/`\n94: \n95: - [ ] **T6.2** Implement `HTTPServer.Start()` method\n96:   - Configure `http.Server` with timeouts\n97:   - Start HTTP server with `ListenAndServe`\n98:   - Return error channel for async error handling\n99:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/`\n100: \n101: - [ ] **T6.3** Implement `HTTPServer.Stop(ctx context.Context)` method\n102:   - Call `http.Server.Shutdown(ctx)`\n103:   - Wait for existing connections to complete\n104:   - Close `stopCh` to signal shutdown complete\n105:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/`\n106: \n107: - [ ] **T6.4** Implement `HTTPServer.GracefulShutdown()` method\n108:   - Setup signal handler for SIGTERM and SIGINT\n109:   - Call `Stop()` on signal\n110:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/`\n111: \n112: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests\n113: \n114: - [ ] **T7.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types_test.go`\n115:   - Test `HandleError` returns correct JSON format\n116:   - Test `SuccessResponse` marshals correctly\n117:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v`\n118: \n119: - [ ] **T7.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go`\n120:   - Test `NewHTTPServer` with default config\n121:   - Test `Start()` and `Stop()` lifecycle\n122:   - Test graceful shutdown with context timeout\n123:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v`\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T7.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/router_test.go`\n126:   - Test `NewRouter()` returns valid router\n127:   - Test `RegisterHandlers()` registers multiple handlers\n128:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v`\n129: \n130: - [ ] **T7.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health_test.go`\n131:   - Test `healthz` returns 200 with `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n132:   - Test `readyz` returns 200 when `IsReady() == true`\n133:   - Test `readyz` returns 503 when `IsReady() == false`\n134:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -v`\n135: \n136: - [ ] **T7.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging_test.go`\n137:   - Test logging middleware captures request method, path, status\n138:   - Test `responseWriterWrapper` captures status code\n139:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/... -v`\n140: \n141: - [ ] **T7.6** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery_test.go`\n142:   - Test recovery middleware catches panic\n143:   - Test recovery middleware returns 500 on panic\n144:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/... -v`\n145: \n146: - [ ] **T7.7** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors_test.go`\n147:   - Test CORS middleware adds `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header\n148:   - Test CORS middleware handles preflight OPTIONS request\n149:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/... -v`\n150: \n151: ### Phase 8: Integration Tests\n152: \n153: - [ ] **T8.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n154:   - Start real HTTP server on random port\n155:   - Send GET request to `/healthz` and verify response\n156:   - Send GET request to `/readyz` and verify response\n157:   - Verify middleware chain executes in correct order\n158:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -tags=integration`\n159: \n160: ### Phase 9: Validation & Quality\n161: \n162: - [ ] **T9.1** Run `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n163:   - Fix any issues reported\n164: \n165: - [ ] **T9.2** Run `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n166:   - Fix any linting issues\n167: \n168: - [ ] **T9.3** Verify HTTP server supports graceful shutdown\n169:   - Send SIGTERM signal to running server\n170:   - Verify server stops accepting new connections\n171:   - Verify existing connections complete within timeout\n172: \n173: - [ ] **T9.4** Verify health endpoints work with Kubernetes probes\n174:   - Test `curl http://localhost:8080/healthz`\n175:   - Test `curl http://localhost:8080/readyz`\n176: \n177: ### Phase 10: Documentation\n178: \n179: - [ ] **T10.1** Add godoc comments to all exported types and functions\n180: - [ ] **T10.2** Add package-level documentation in `pkg/workloadmanager/doc.go`\n181: - [ ] **T10.3** Document middleware execution order in `README.md` or design notes\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## Task Dependencies\n186: \n187: ```\n188: T1.1 → T1.2 → T2.1 → T2.2 → T3.1 → T4.1 → T4.2\n189:                                             ↓\n190:                           T5.1 → T5.2 → T5.3\n191:                                             ↓\n192:                           T6.1 → T6.2 → T6.3 → T6.4\n193:                                             ↓\n194:                           T7.1 → T7.2 → T7.3 → T7.4 → T7.5 → T7.6 → T7.7\n195:                                             ↓\n196:                                           T8.1\n197:                                             ↓\n198:                           T9.1 → T9.2 → T9.3 → T9.4\n199:                                             ↓\n200:                           T10.1 → T10.2 → T10.3\n201: ```\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## Verification Commands\n206: \n207: | Task | Verification Command |\n208: |------|----------------------|\n209: | T1.2 | `go mod tidy && go mod verify` |\n210: | T2.1-T6.4 | `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n211: | T7.1-T7.7 | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v` |\n212: | T8.1 | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -tags=integration` |\n213: | T9.1 | `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n214: | T9.2 | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n215: | T9.3 | `kill -SIGTERM <pid>` and observe logs |\n216: | T9.4 | `curl http://localhost:8080/healthz` |\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ## Acceptance Criteria\n221: \n222: - [ ] HTTP server starts on configured address\n223: - [ ] HTTP server supports graceful shutdown\n224: - [ ] Router framework supports route grouping and middleware\n225: - [ ] Health check endpoints (`/healthz`, `/readyz`) respond correctly\n226: - [ ] Middleware chain executes in correct order\n227: - [ ] Error responses use unified JSON format\n228: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n229: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n230: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n231: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ## Notes\n236: \n237: - Use `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` for routing\n238: - Follow Go standard library conventions for HTTP handlers\n239: - Graceful shutdown timeout should be configurable (default 30s)\n240: - Middleware should use standard `func(http.Handler) http.Handler` signature\n241: - Health check implementation should support dependency checking (via `HealthChecker` interface)\n\n(End of file - total 241 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-1 pending] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Project Setup\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create directory structure `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n  - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/tasks.m